        "description": "This project creates a portable battery pack glove for a mini drill machine or similar handheld devices. It provides a convenient and mobile power source for short-term use.",
        "steps": [
            "Connect three 9V batteries in series using 9V battery connectors to create a battery pack, ensuring you have a positive and negative terminal.",
            "Cut the power adapter wire (salvaged from a broken adapter if necessary) to the desired length.",
            "Remove the outer insulation from the wire and strip the inner black (positive) and red (negative) wires.",
            "Connect the stripped wires from the adapter to the corresponding wires from the battery pack.",
            "Solder the connections securely and cover them with electrical tape for insulation.",
            "Cut up one glove and use it to make a pocket on the back of the other glove to hold the batteries.",
            "Cut up a finger from the glove and make a flap with a button to secure the batteries in the pocket.",
            "Stitch the pocket and flap onto the glove.",
            "Insert the batteries into the pocket and close the flap.",
